        options: ["Discharge the patient once respiratory rate normalizes","Monitor for at least 4-6 hours because methadone's half-life exceeds naloxone's duration","Restart methadone at the same dose the following day","Administer a single dose of flumazenil to maintain wakefulness"],
        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Naloxone's half-life (30-90 minutes) is much shorter than methadone's half-life (8-59 hours). Re-sedation and respiratory depression will recur as naloxone wears off. Continuous monitoring for at least 4-6 hours and possible repeated naloxone dosing or continuous infusion are required."
