        correct: 1,
        rationale: "The first 3-5 days of methadone induction carry the highest risk of fatal overdose because methadone accumulates due to its long and variable half-life. Peak respiratory depressant effect occurs later and lasts longer than peak analgesic effect, and steady state is not reached for 5-7 days or longer."
