        rationale: "Capillary refill time and skin mottling score directly reflect microcirculatory perfusion at the tissue level. The ANDROMEDA-SHOCK trial validated CRT as a resuscitation target. MAP, CVP, and cardiac output are macrocirculatory parameters that may not reflect microcirculatory status."
