        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Budesonide should be tapered gradually (3 mg reduction every 2-4 weeks) after achieving remission. Abrupt discontinuation risks adrenal insufficiency and rapid relapse. Since 60-80% of patients relapse after stopping budesonide, many require long-term maintenance at 3-6 mg daily."
